citations:
    citation-affc-the-iron-captain-i:
        source: source-affc
        properties:
            locator: "The Iron Captain"
            text_from_source: "No man had ever loved his wives half as well as the Lord Captain loved his ships."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "POV: Victarion Greyjoy. Chapter title: The Iron Captain. Victarion arrives at Old Wyk with the Iron Fleet for the Kingsmoot. He was holding Moat Cailin (left Ralf Kenning in command). He is greeted by Aeron Damphair. At a feast that night, Victarion hosts captains: Fralegg the Strong, Alvyn Sharp, Hotho Harlaw (humpbacked, offers a daughter aged 12 as bride). Baelor Blacktyde counsels peace with the Iron Throne. Asha Greyjoy arrives unexpectedly, having beached Black Wind and ridden across Old Wyk. Euron Crow's Eye arrives with his followers: Pinchface Jon Myre, Torwold Browntooth, Left-Hand Lucas Codd, Germund Botley, Orkwood of Orkmont, Stonehand, Quellon Humble, the Red Oarsman, Ralf the Shepherd, Ralf of Lordsport, Qarl the Thrall. Key description of Euron: black hair, one black eyepatch over left eye, blue right eye ('smiling eye'), bruised-looking lips. Euron's ship Silence described: dark red hull, black sails, iron maiden figurehead with no mouth, crewed entirely by mutes and 'monsters' from across the world. Victarion killed his third wife (Euron violated her; Victarion beat her to death to preserve honor). Victarion confirms he gave up Moat Cailin when the kingsmoot summons came."
